President Obama's announcement that he will attend the United Nations Climate Change Conference in Copenhagen and propose a U.S. emissions reduction target has received immediate support from a diverse group of leaders. Former Vice President Al Gore and Senator John Kerry praised the President for taking action and showing leadership on climate change. Other senators and representatives also expressed their support and commended the President for his commitment. CEOs of energy companies and environmental organizations also applauded the President's efforts and called for Congress to pass clean energy and climate protection legislation. Overall, the announcement is seen as a significant step towards reaching a global agreement on climate change.